Nelson Mandela saw English Premier division club  Liverpool score the second victory of their South African soccer safari here  Thursday, defeating Cape Town Spurs 3-0.
South Africa's new president was among the capacity 20,000 crowd who saw  Liverpool coast to victory in the first football match staged at Newlands  cricket stadium.
England youth international Robbie Fowler scored after five and 50 minutes  and Neil Ruddock netted in the dying seconds for Liverpool on a surface made  treacherous by persistent driving rain.
Liverpool complete their tour Sunday in Johannesburg against Kaizer Chiefs  and another English side, Aston Villa, will play Moroka Swallows in the  curtain raiser.
